2.MySql VS SQL

SQL extends for Structured Query Language. SQL is a standard language that enables the user to design and manage databases.
On the other hand, MySQL is a relational database management system that allows a user to store and retrieve data from the database.
MySQL uses SQL to perform specific operations on the database. 
Both MySQL and SQL offer two trendy and differentiable servers: MySQL server and SQL Server for database management.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3.MAC(Media Access Control Address) Address-:

MAC Address is used to ensure the physical address of a computer.
MAC Address operates in the data link layer.


IP Address(Internet Protocol Address.)

IP Address is the logical address of the computer.
	IP Address operates in the network layer.